refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
intimagecolorresolvealpha GdImageimage intred intgreen intblue intalpha
This function is guaranteed to return a color index for a requested color, either the exact color or the closest possible alternative.

  &reftitle.parameters;



    &gd.image.description;

     red


&gd.value.red;



     green


&gd.value.green;



     blue


&gd.value.blue;



     alpha



       A value between 0 and 127.
       0 indicates completely opaque while 
       127 indicates completely transparent.




   The colors parameters are integers between 0 and 255 or hexadecimals
   between 0x00 and 0xFF.

  &reftitle.examples;

   Using imagecoloresolvealpha to get colors from an image


<?php
// Load an image
$im = imagecreatefromgif('phplogo.gif');

// Get closest colors from the image
$colors = array();
$colors[] = imagecolorresolvealpha($im, 255, 255, 255, 0);
$colors[] = imagecolorresolvealpha($im, 0, 0, 200, 127);

// Output
print_r($colors);

imagedestroy($im);
?>


   &example.outputs.similar;


Array
(
    [0] => 89
    [1] => 85
)
